PRODUCT: AAC(6')-Ib-cr is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids transposons integrons in Enterobacteriaceae. The aac(6')-Ib-cr variant gene can induce resistance against aminoglycoside and fluoroquinolone simultaneously
ANT(3'')-IIa is a aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase identified in Acinetobacter spp. via horizontal gene transfer mechanisms.
